
The purposes of this study were to discover and compare patients' and nurses' perceptions of the learning needs of cancer zzso Using rating zzso 33 nurses and 27 patients rated the degree of importance of learning 36 informational items, including nutrition, treatment, and diagnostic zzso In addition, nurses and patients ranked six content areas according to: how problematic each area was for the zzso how much knowledge the patient had about each area; and how much the patient wanted information about each zzso zzso indicated that significant differences existed between nurses' and patients' perceptions of the learning needs of cancer zzso Nurses rated the degree of importance of the 20 general information items significantly higher than did the zzso The rank order of the six content areas for each of three questions by nurses and patients showed nurses ranked dealing with feelings as the most problematic area for patients, while patients ranked this area zzso 

